      {
        "unique_name": "definition_activity_02VJQTIVFH2J65gZOmdRFOZ2DcnkK72aVTB",
        "name": "Meraki - Create Organization Network",
        "title": "Meraki - Create Organization Network",
        "type": "workflow.atomic_workflow",
        "base_type": "subworkflow",
        "properties": {
          "atomic": {
            "atomic_group": "Cisco Meraki",
            "atomic_subgroup": "Networks"
          },
          "continue_on_failure": false,
          "description": "**Cisco Meraki - Networks - Create Network**\n\nCreate a network in Meraki Organization. To create a combined network, select more than one Product Types task will automatically create the network as combined type.\n\n**Target:** A Meraki Endpoint using HTTPS \"api.meraki.com\" port 443 and no path.\n\n**Account Key:** Meraki User API Key. API Key can be generated from Meraki Dashboard -> User Profile -> API Access.\n\nSteps:\n[] Sends Create Network request to Meraki\n[] Check if the request was successful:\n[]> If it was, attempt to extract the results and set the output variables\n[]> If it wasn't, check if \"Ignore If Exits\" input is set to true.\n[]>> If it was, skips the \"name already exits\" error and marks the workflow as completed successfully.\n[]>> If it wasn't, return the error and marks the workflow as failed.\n\nNOTE: Empty attributes in the request are removed from the payload before sending to Meraki. \n\nMore information about this API: https://developer.cisco.com/meraki/api-v1/create-organization-network/",
          "display_name": "Meraki - Create Organization Network",
          "input": {
            "variable_workflow_02JJPT9HBQPQ60olVVxRFCRUe38ZJHZw7G0": "$activity.definition_activity_02VJR1DIP93Y673jSSgthCbf63cx0BmInnI.output.prompt_response.Network name$",
