      {
        "unique_name": "definition_activity_02VJSC27W2ZY51pT0OvojPU3OTph4awxf1Q",
        "name": "Meraki - Claim Network Devices",
        "title": "Meraki - Claim Network Devices",
        "type": "workflow.atomic_workflow",
        "base_type": "subworkflow",
        "properties": {
          "atomic": {
            "atomic_group": "Cisco Meraki",
            "atomic_subgroup": "Devices"
          },
          "continue_on_failure": false,
          "description": "**Cisco Meraki - Devices - Claim Network Devices**\n\nClaim devices into a network. (Note: for recently claimed devices, it may take a few minutes for API requests against that device to succeed). This operation can be used up to ten times within a single five minute window.\n\n**Target:** A Meraki Endpoint using HTTPS \"api.meraki.com\" port 443 and no path.\n\n**Account Key:** Meraki User API Key. API Key can be generated from Meraki Dashboard -> User Profile -> API Access.\n\nSteps:\n[] Sends request to Meraki\n[] Check if the request was successful:\n[]> If it was, attempt to extract the results and set the output variables\n[]> If it wasn't, check if \"Ignore If Exits\" input is set to true.\n[]>> If it was, skips the \"already claimed\" error and marks the workflow as completed successfully.\n[]>> If it wasn't, return the error and marks the workflow as failed.\n\nMore information about this API: https://developer.cisco.com/meraki/api-v1/claim-network-devices/",
